<exercise number="49"><statement><p> In a reflecting telescope a parabolic mirror is used to collect light, and the image forms at the focus of the parabola. Suppose you want to build a parabolic mirror that is 72 inches in diameter and 3 inches deep.</p>
<p><ol label="a">
    <li>Find an equation for the parabola.</li>
    <li>How far is the focus from the vertex of the parabola?</li></ol></p>

<sidebyside widths="40%"><image source="images/fig-10-1-hp49.png"><description>telescope</description></image></sidebyside>
</statement>

    <answer><p><ol label = "a">
        <li><m>x^2=432y</m></li>
        <li>108 in</li></ol></p>   </answer></exercise>

